{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# AI Interview Coach – Backend on Colab\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the backend with a **larger LLM model** on Colab's GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this does\n",
    "- Installs Ollama and pulls a bigger model (e.g. `qwen2.5:14b`)\n",
    "- Installs Python dependencies\n",
    "- Clones your backend code from GitHub\n",
    "- Configures the `.env` to use the bigger model and GPU\n",
    "- Starts the FastAPI server behind an **ngrok tunnel** so your frontend can reach it\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 – Clone the backend repo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!git clone https://github.com/Abdul-Wahab1210/AI-Interview-Coach-Backend.git /content/backend\n",
    "%cd /content/backend"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 – Install Ollama & pull a large model\n",
    "\n",
    "You have **48 GB RAM** — you can run much better models:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | Quality | RAM needed | Best for |\n",
    "|-------|---------|------------|---------|\n",
    "| `qwen2.5:14b` | High | ~16 GB | **Good balance** |\n",
    "| `llama3.1:8b` | Good | ~12 GB | Fast & reliable |\n",
    "| `mixtral:8x7b` | Very high | ~26 GB | Best quality on your RAM |\n",
    "| `deepseek-r1:32b` | Excellent | ~40 GB | Cutting-edge reasoning |\n",
    "\n",
    "Set `MODEL_NAME` below:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pick your model -------------------------------------------------\n",
    "MODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:14b\"       # ← recommended: great quality, fits easily\n",
    "# MODEL_NAME = \"llama3.1:8b\"    # good, faster\n",
    "# MODEL_NAME = \"mixtral:8x7b\"  # very high quality, uses ~26GB\n",
    "# MODEL_NAME = \"deepseek-r1:32b\"  # best reasoning, uses ~40GB\n",
    "# ----------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Will install Ollama and pull {MODEL_NAME}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\n",
    "!ollama serve &>/dev/null &\n",
    "!sleep 5\n",
    "!ollama pull {MODEL_NAME}\n",
    "print(f\"Ollama ready with {MODEL_NAME}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 – Install Python dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -r requirements.txt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 – Configure .env for the big model + GPU"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "env = f'''\n",
    "DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./data/interview_coach.db\n",
    "SECRET_KEY=d5ab43cbbfc268ebb51fd090e7331a437b828504f4be8e3fb099cf0683da1da8\n",
    "ALGORITHM=HS256\n",
    "ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440\n",
    "OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434\n",
    "OLLAMA_MODEL={MODEL_NAME}\n",
    "OLLAMA_EVALUATION_MODEL={MODEL_NAME}\n",
    "OLLAMA_QUESTION_MODEL={MODEL_NAME}\n",
    "WHISPER_MODEL_SIZE=large-v3\n",
    "WHISPER_DEVICE=cuda\n",
    "WHISPER_COMPUTE_TYPE=float16\n",
    "'''\n",
    "with open('.env', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(env.strip())\n",
    "print('.env updated')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5 – Open CORS for ngrok"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "main = open('app/main.py').read()\n",
    "main = main.replace('allow_origins=[\"http://localhost:5173\"]', 'allow_origins=[\"*\"]')\n",
    "open('app/main.py', 'w').write(main)\n",
    "print('CORS opened')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6 – Install ngrok & start everything"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!wget -q https://bin.equinox.io/c/bNyj1mQVY4c/ngrok-v3-stable-linux-amd64.tgz\n",
    "!tar -xzf ngrok-v3-stable-linux-amd64.tgz\n",
    "!mv ngrok /usr/local/bin/\n",
    "!nohup uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 &\n",
    "!sleep 3\n",
    "!nohup ngrok http 8000 --log=stdout &\n",
    "!sleep 3\n",
    "\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "tunnels = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:4040/api/tunnels').json()\n",
    "url = tunnels['tunnels'][0]['public_url']\n",
    "print('=' * 60)\n",
    "print(f'  BACKEND LIVE: {url}')\n",
    "print(f'  Health check: {url}/health')\n",
    "print('=' * 60)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Frontend setup\n",
    "\n",
    "In `frontend/.env` add:\n",
    "```\n",
    "VITE_API_URL=https://xxxx-xxxx-xxxx.ngrok-free.app\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "*(URL changes every Colab restart)*\n",
    "\n",
    "## Stop services when done\n",
    "```\n",
    "!pkill ngrok; pkill uvicorn; pkill ollama\n",
    "```"
 ],
